President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of New York due to severe storms, straight-line winds, and flooding that occurred from October 31 to November 1, 2019. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts. The affected areas include 19 counties in New York. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Robert Little III has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made based on damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.